  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to medium-high, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (make sure the chicken isn't overlapping!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and the <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your <strong>BBQ chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1607345429262-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1607345429262-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1607345429262-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1607345429262-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1607345429262-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up so that the chicken is fully coated and put it under the grill for 20 min or until the chicken is cooked through and caramelised (no pink meat!)</p><p>While the chicken is grilling, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1607345438579-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1607345438579-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1607345438579-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1607345438579-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1607345438579-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>to a bowl and mix everything together</p><p>Crumble in the<strong> feta</strong>,<strong> </strong>season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir to combine – this is your<strong> fritter mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1607345443524-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1607345443524-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1607345443524-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1607345443524-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1607345443524-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, spoon the <strong>fritter mixture</strong> into the pan, roughly divided into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>and cook for 4 min on one side then 2 min on the other until golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>spicy sweetcorn fritters</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1607345453427-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
